# North Star alignment + AI context

## For any AI working on this repo

Read **`PROJECT_BRAIN.md`** for a stable system summary, then **`AGENTS.md`**. For subsystem depth, see **`docs/MODULE_SWEEP_STATUS.md`** and the linked **`docs/*_MODULE_SECOND_SWEEP.md`** for the area you change. `AGENTS.md` contains:
- The complete file map (where everything lives)
- Hard rules (what never to break)
- Code style guide
- How to add tools, aspects, and routes
- What documents to keep updated

## Source of truth

- **`LAYLA_NORTH_STAR.md`** — full vision §1–§20. All features and decisions must align with it. Do not modify unless the operator explicitly asks.
- **`docs/IMPLEMENTATION_STATUS.md`** — maps each §1–§20 to actual code files and verification status. Check here before implementing anything.
- **`ARCHITECTURE.md`** — one-page request flow and state map. Keep updated when the flow changes.

## When adding or changing behavior

1. Check which North Star §§ it falls under (`docs/IMPLEMENTATION_STATUS.md`)
2. Implement or extend the mapped components
3. Update `ARCHITECTURE.md` if request flow changes
4. Update `docs/IMPLEMENTATION_STATUS.md` if a section is newly implemented
5. Run tests: `cd agent && pytest tests/ -x -q`

Safe self-upgrade: approval flow gates writes/runs; `add_learning` for memory; Lilith gates autonomy.
